TY  - JOUR
AU  - Sandler, Todd
AU  - Murdoch, James C.
T1  - Nash-Cournot or Lindahl Behavior?: An Empirical Test for the NATO Allies*
PY  - 1990
Y1  - 1990/11/01
DO  - 10.2307/2937877
JO  - The Quarterly Journal of Economics
JA  - Q J Econ
VL  - 105
IS  - 4
SP  - 875
EP  - 894
SN  - 0033-5533
AB  - This paper derives systems of demand equations for distinguishing between Nash-Cournot and Lindahl behavior in a group that either shares a pure public good or an activity that provides a private and a pure public joint product. Systems of simultaneous equations are estimated based upon Nash-Cournot and Lindahl behavior for a sample of ten NATO allies for the 1956–1987 period. Nonnested hypothesis tests support the Nash-Cournot specification for five of the ten sample allies. No evidence of Lindahl behavior is found. The Nash-Cournot joint-product specification outperforms the pure public model for all sample allies.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.2307/2937877
ER  - 



